cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper deals with machine translation, specifically the translation of pronouns from English to French. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of rule-based, statistical, and neural machine translation systems, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The evaluation of the different systems also involves analyzing the functional and referential properties of pronouns, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
